==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twain
<hw>Twain</hw> <pr>(tw⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a. & n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>twein</ets>, <ets>tweien</ets>, <ets>tweyne</ets>, AS.
<ets>tw⟦emac⟧gen</ets>, masc. See <er>Two</er>.]</ety> <def>Two; --
nearly obsolete in common discourse, but used in poetry and
burlesque.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Children <xex>twain</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And whosoever shall compel thee to go a mile, go with him
<qex>twain</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. v. 41.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>In twain</b></col>, <cd>in halves; into two parts;
asunder.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When old winter split the rocks in <qex>twain</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <col><b>Twain cloud</b></col>. <fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <cd>Same as
<er>Cumulo-stratus</er>.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Twaite</ent>⟦br⟧
